message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a 3D convolutional neural network for the segmentation of abdominal aortic aneurysms from preoperative and postoperative CTA scans. This involves image analysis and medical imaging, which are typically covered in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on medical applications and the analysis of medical images, which are covered in the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. The use of a neural network also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NEURON) sub-categories.
